cs.LO, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with proof nets for a logical calculus, namely the Lambek calculus. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper explores the generative capacity of the Lambek-Grishin calculus, which is relevant to natural language processing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the Lambek calculus has been used in natural language understanding and reasoning tasks. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the structure of proof nets. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also less likely but possible as the paper presents an embedding of lexicalized tree adjoining grammars into the Lambek-Grishin calculus, which is relevant to formal language theory.
